<table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" ><tr ><td valign="top" width="650" ><div class="mktEditable" id="left-column" ><p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">2015 is officially closed and it proved to be a volatile year. At the OEM level, we saw a new CEO appointment at Bell Helicopter, United Technologies divested Sikorsky and across all the major OEMs, lowered production levels, primarily within the twin-engine classes. At the aftermarket level, the industry saw deferments of retrofits, modifications and upgrades, increased quantities of parked/idle aircraft and in some missions, lower flight utilization; and lastly, operators primarily within the United States, are beginning to comply with the FAA HEMS and ADS-B Out mandates.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Despite a challenging 2015, Honeywell experienced overall positive growth, anchored primarily within the aftermarket business. This growth in a constrained market can be directly attributed to Honeywell providing differentiating products and services as well as providing cost effective safety solution sets which meet the latest FAA regulatory HEMS and ADS-B Out mandate requirements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">While the overall industry consensus reflects continued challenges in 2016, we are committed to increasing our differentiating and mandate solutions through a robust STC expansion plan. Our goal is to ensure all operators are not only able to weather this storm, but also allow them to become more competitive and safer in their operations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">We look forward to meeting each of you at HAI HELI-EXPO in Louisville, Kentucky [Booth 4945] and together, we will do our part to make this industry positive going forward.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">We&rsquo;re bringing you the&nbsp;<strong style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Possibilities of Vertical Flight</strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">.</span><em style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;Made Easy.</em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"></span><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Sincerely,</span></span><br /><span style="font-size: 12px;"><em><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Rick Angelo</span></em></span><br /><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;">Director of Strategic Marketing: Global Commercial Helicopters</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px;"></span><br /></p>
